is most similar to the female of 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961D456A5EC8FB40FE3DFB43" authority="(Strobl, 1910)" baseAuthorityName="Strobl" baseAuthorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscuripes">
<emphasis id="78D38832961D456A5EC8FB40FE80FB43" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">E. obscuripes</emphasis>
(Strobl, 1910)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="D29C48A5961D456A5B83FB61FDC9FB42" box="[451,576,1210,1237]" captionStart="Figs 53–58" captionStartId="15.[174,213,1303,1325]" captionTargetBox="[206,1200,172,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-191@15.[206,1200,172,1279]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 53–58. Epistrophe obscuripes female (Moscow Region, Russia): 53 — habitus, dorsal view; 54 — apex of the hind femur, lateral view (arrow shows yellow macrotrichia); 55 — hind tibia, lateral view; 56 — head, lateral view; 57 — head, anterolateral view; 58 — head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455548/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">figs 53–58</figureCitation>
) in sharing the following characters: basal medial (
<emphasis id="78D38832961D456A5EE1FB61FB4FFB43" box="[1185,1222,1210,1236]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">bm</emphasis>
) cell of wing entirely covered in microtrichia; mesoscutum mostly brightly shining, without distinct pruinescence dorsally; tergite 5 partly black; scutellum with only yellow macrotrichia or with just a few black macrotrichia along hind margin; frons entirely black (
<figureCitation id="D29C48A5961D456A5EE5FAC1FF7EFAC2" captionStart="Figs 47–52" captionStartId="14.[166,205,1411,1433]" captionTargetBox="[198,1192,174,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-160@14.[198,1192,174,1383]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 47–52. Epistrophe cryptica female:47 — habitus, dorsal view; 48 — apex of the hind femur, lateral view (arrow shows black macrotrichia); 49 — hind tibia, lateral view; 50 — head, lateral view; 51 — head, anterolateral view; 52 — head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455546/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">figs 51, 52</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="D29C48A5961D456A5B44FAE1FEC7FAC2" box="[260,334,1338,1365]" captionStart="Figs 53–58" captionStartId="15.[174,213,1303,1325]" captionTargetBox="[206,1200,172,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-191@15.[206,1200,172,1279]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 53–58. Epistrophe obscuripes female (Moscow Region, Russia): 53 — habitus, dorsal view; 54 — apex of the hind femur, lateral view (arrow shows yellow macrotrichia); 55 — hind tibia, lateral view; 56 — head, lateral view; 57 — head, anterolateral view; 58 — head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455548/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">57, 58</figureCitation>
); anterior side of hind tibia entirely or partly with yellow macrotrichia (
<figureCitation id="D29C48A5961D456A5EE5FAE1FF45FAE3" captionStart="Figs 47–52" captionStartId="14.[166,205,1411,1433]" captionTargetBox="[198,1192,174,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-160@14.[198,1192,174,1383]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 47–52. Epistrophe cryptica female:47 — habitus, dorsal view; 48 — apex of the hind femur, lateral view (arrow shows black macrotrichia); 49 — hind tibia, lateral view; 50 — head, lateral view; 51 — head, anterolateral view; 52 — head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455546/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">figs 49</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="D29C48A5961D456A5A9BFA81FF72FAE2" box="[219,251,1370,1397]" captionStart="Figs 53–58" captionStartId="15.[174,213,1303,1325]" captionTargetBox="[206,1200,172,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-191@15.[206,1200,172,1279]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 53–58. Epistrophe obscuripes female (Moscow Region, Russia): 53 — habitus, dorsal view; 54 — apex of the hind femur, lateral view (arrow shows yellow macrotrichia); 55 — hind tibia, lateral view; 56 — head, lateral view; 57 — head, anterolateral view; 58 — head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455548/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">55</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961D456A5B52FA81FE7AFAE3" authorityName="Doczkal and Schmid" authorityYear="1994" box="[274,499,1370,1396]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cryptica">
<emphasis id="78D38832961D456A5B52FA81FE7AFAE3" box="[274,499,1370,1396]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">Epistrophe cryptica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961D456A5903FA80FC55FAE3" baseAuthorityName="Strobl" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[835,988,1370,1396]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscuripes">
<emphasis id="78D38832961D456A5903FA80FC55FAE3" box="[835,988,1370,1396]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">E. obscuripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by: arista yellow, at least in basal half (
<figureCitation id="D29C48A5961D456A5BC5FAA1FE58FA02" box="[389,465,1402,1429]" captionStart="Figs 47–52" captionStartId="14.[166,205,1411,1433]" captionTargetBox="[198,1192,174,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-160@14.[198,1192,174,1383]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 47–52. Epistrophe cryptica female:47 — habitus, dorsal view; 48 — apex of the hind femur, lateral view (arrow shows black macrotrichia); 49 — hind tibia, lateral view; 50 — head, lateral view; 51 — head, anterolateral view; 52 — head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455546/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">fig. 51</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961D456A5849FAA0FD17FA03" baseAuthorityName="Strobl" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[521,670,1402,1428]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscuripes">
<emphasis id="78D38832961D456A5849FAA0FD17FA03" box="[521,670,1402,1428]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">E. obscuripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, arista entirely black, as in 
<figureCitation id="D29C48A5961D456A599DFAA1FBAEFA02" box="[989,1063,1402,1429]" captionStart="Figs 53–58" captionStartId="15.[174,213,1303,1325]" captionTargetBox="[206,1200,172,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-191@15.[206,1200,172,1279]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 53–58. Epistrophe obscuripes female (Moscow Region, Russia): 53 — habitus, dorsal view; 54 — apex of the hind femur, lateral view (arrow shows yellow macrotrichia); 55 — hind tibia, lateral view; 56 — head, lateral view; 57 — head, anterolateral view; 58 — head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455548/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">fig. 57</figureCitation>
); anterior side of hind femur with black macrotrichia apically (
<figureCitation id="D29C48A5961D456A58ACFA41FCB1FA23" box="[748,824,1434,1460]" captionStart="Figs 47–52" captionStartId="14.[166,205,1411,1433]" captionTargetBox="[198,1192,174,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-160@14.[198,1192,174,1383]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 47–52. Epistrophe cryptica female:47 — habitus, dorsal view; 48 — apex of the hind femur, lateral view (arrow shows black macrotrichia); 49 — hind tibia, lateral view; 50 — head, lateral view; 51 — head, anterolateral view; 52 — head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455546/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">fig. 48</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961D456A5934FA40FB82FA23" baseAuthorityName="Strobl" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[884,1035,1434,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscuripes">
<emphasis id="78D38832961D456A5934FA40FB82FA23" box="[884,1035,1434,1460]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">E. obscuripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, anterior side of hind femur almost only with yellow macrotrichia, as in 
<figureCitation id="D29C48A5961D456A5901FA61FC04FA42" box="[833,909,1466,1493]" captionStart="Figs 53–58" captionStartId="15.[174,213,1303,1325]" captionTargetBox="[206,1200,172,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-191@15.[206,1200,172,1279]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 53–58. Epistrophe obscuripes female (Moscow Region, Russia): 53 — habitus, dorsal view; 54 — apex of the hind femur, lateral view (arrow shows yellow macrotrichia); 55 — hind tibia, lateral view; 56 — head, lateral view; 57 — head, anterolateral view; 58 — head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455548/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">fig. 54</figureCitation>
); anterior side of hind tibia covered in a mixture of black and yellow macrotrichia (
<figureCitation id="D29C48A5961D456A5904FA01FC18FA63" box="[836,913,1498,1524]" captionStart="Figs 47–52" captionStartId="14.[166,205,1411,1433]" captionTargetBox="[198,1192,174,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-160@14.[198,1192,174,1383]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 47–52. Epistrophe cryptica female:47 — habitus, dorsal view; 48 — apex of the hind femur, lateral view (arrow shows black macrotrichia); 49 — hind tibia, lateral view; 50 — head, lateral view; 51 — head, anterolateral view; 52 — head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455546/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">fig. 49</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961D456A598BFA00FBEBFA63" baseAuthorityName="Strobl" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[971,1122,1498,1524]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscuripes">
<emphasis id="78D38832961D456A598BFA00FBEBFA63" box="[971,1122,1498,1524]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">E. obscuripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, anterior side of hind tibia entirely covered in yellow macrotrichia, as in 
<figureCitation id="D29C48A5961D456A59D0FA21FC52F982" box="[912,987,1530,1557]" captionStart="Figs 53–58" captionStartId="15.[174,213,1303,1325]" captionTargetBox="[206,1200,172,1279]" captionTargetId="figure-191@15.[206,1200,172,1279]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figs 53–58. Epistrophe obscuripes female (Moscow Region, Russia): 53 — habitus, dorsal view; 54 — apex of the hind femur, lateral view (arrow shows yellow macrotrichia); 55 — hind tibia, lateral view; 56 — head, lateral view; 57 — head, anterolateral view; 58 — head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455548" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455548/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">fig. 55</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A185420961D45695AA3F9C1FC65F9CC" blockId="13.[174,1233,954,1845]" lastBlockId="14.[166,1225,1536,1851]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="251" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">
The species is also very similar in appearance to 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961D456A5969F9C0FB42F9A3" authority="(Zetterstedt, 1843)" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[809,1227,1562,1588]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanostoma">
<emphasis id="78D38832961D456A5969F9C0FC6CF9A3" box="[809,997,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">E. melanostoma</emphasis>
(Zetterstedt, 1843)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961D456A5AEEF9E0FD8BF9C3" authority="(Meigen, 1822)" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[174,514,1594,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidicollis">
<emphasis id="78D38832961D456A5AEEF9E0FECFF9C3" box="[174,326,1594,1620]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">E. nitidicollis</emphasis>
(Meigen, 1822)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961D456A587DF9E0FCBDF9C3" authority="Mutin, 1990" authorityName="Mutin" authorityYear="1990" box="[573,820,1594,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olgae">
<emphasis id="78D38832961D456A587DF9E0FD10F9C3" box="[573,665,1594,1620]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">E. olgae</emphasis>
Mutin, 1990
</taxonomicName>
. From 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961D456A59C9F9E0FBA8F9C3" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[905,1057,1594,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidicollis">
<emphasis id="78D38832961D456A59C9F9E0FBA8F9C3" box="[905,1057,1594,1620]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">E. nitidicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961D456A5E1DF9E0FB31F9C3" authorityName="Mutin" authorityYear="1990" box="[1117,1208,1594,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olgae">
<emphasis id="78D38832961D456A5E1DF9E0FB31F9C3" box="[1117,1208,1594,1620]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">E. olgae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it differs by: wing entirely covered in microtrichia (in others, wing with basal medial (
<emphasis id="78D38832961D456A5EE1F981FB4FF9E3" box="[1185,1222,1626,1652]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">bm</emphasis>
) cell 20% or more bare of microtrichia); scutellum with only yellow macrotrichia or with just a few black macrotrichia along hind margin (in others, at least one third of the scutellum with black macrotrichia); frons entirely black with gray pruinescence that do not look like separate maculae (
<figureCitation id="D29C48A5961D456A5BFDF901FDB3F962" box="[445,570,1754,1781]" captionStart="Figs 47–52" captionStartId="14.[166,205,1411,1433]" captionTargetBox="[198,1192,174,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-160@14.[198,1192,174,1383]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 47–52. Epistrophe cryptica female:47 — habitus, dorsal view; 48 — apex of the hind femur, lateral view (arrow shows black macrotrichia); 49 — hind tibia, lateral view; 50 — head, lateral view; 51 — head, anterolateral view; 52 — head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455546/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">figs 51, 52</figureCitation>
) (in others, frons with yellow anterior part and usually with two well developed yellowish-gray or golden-yellow maculae of pruinescens; in 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961D456A5ED3F920FF5DF8A3" authorityName="Mutin" authorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="250" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olgae">
<emphasis id="78D38832961D456A5ED3F920FF5DF8A3" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="250">E. olgae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, frons entirely with dense pruinescence except for the anterior part, and the maculae along the compound eye margin often merge almost into a continuous band). Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961E45695AE6F9FAFEA8F9AD" authorityName="Doczkal and Schmid" authorityYear="1994" box="[166,289,1569,1594]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cryptica">
<emphasis id="78D38832961E45695AE6F9FAFEA8F9AD" box="[166,289,1569,1594]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="251">E. cryptica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961E45695B83F9FAFDD2F9AD" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[451,603,1568,1594]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidicollis">
<emphasis id="78D38832961E45695B83F9FAFDD2F9AD" box="[451,603,1568,1594]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="251">E. nitidicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the yellow arista, at least in basal half (
<figureCitation id="D29C48A5961E45695E0BF9FBFB1EF9AC" box="[1099,1175,1568,1595]" captionStart="Figs 47–52" captionStartId="14.[166,205,1411,1433]" captionTargetBox="[198,1192,174,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-160@14.[198,1192,174,1383]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 47–52. Epistrophe cryptica female:47 — habitus, dorsal view; 48 — apex of the hind femur, lateral view (arrow shows black macrotrichia); 49 — hind tibia, lateral view; 50 — head, lateral view; 51 — head, anterolateral view; 52 — head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455546/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="251">fig. 51</figureCitation>
) (in 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961E45695AE6F99AFEB4F9CD" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[166,317,1600,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidicollis">
<emphasis id="78D38832961E45695AE6F99AFEB4F9CD" box="[166,317,1600,1626]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="251">E. nitidicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the arista is black, rarely it can be brownish or yellowish).
</paragraph>
<caption id="1ED804A8961E45695AE6FA58FE41FA59" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455546" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6455546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455546/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="251" startId="14.[166,205,1411,1433]" targetBox="[198,1192,174,1383]" targetPageId="14">
<paragraph id="4A185420961E45695AE6FA58FE41FA59" blockId="14.[166,1225,1411,1486]" pageId="14" pageNumber="251">
Figs 47–52. 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961E45695B57FA58FE45FA0E" authorityName="Doczkal and Schmid" authorityYear="1994" box="[279,460,1411,1433]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cryptica">
<emphasis id="78D38832961E45695B57FA58FE45FA0E" box="[279,460,1411,1433]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="251">Epistrophe cryptica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
female: 47 — habitus, dorsal view; 48 — apex of the hind femur, lateral view (arrow shows black macrotrichia); 49 — hind tibia, lateral view; 50 — head, lateral view; 51 — head, anterolateral view; 52 — head, frontal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="4A185420961E45695A9BF9BBFBDBF8AC" blockId="14.[166,1225,1536,1851]" pageId="14" pageNumber="251">
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961E45695A9BF9BBFE33F9ED" authorityName="Doczkal and Schmid" authorityYear="1994" box="[219,442,1632,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cryptica">
<emphasis id="78D38832961E45695A9BF9BBFE33F9ED" box="[219,442,1632,1658]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="251">Epistrophe cryptica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961E456958CCF9BAFCCEF9ED" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[652,839,1632,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanostoma">
<emphasis id="78D38832961E456958CCF9BAFCCEF9ED" box="[652,839,1632,1658]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="251">E. melanostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having: wing entirely covered in microtrichia; scutellum with only yellow macrotrichia or with just a few black macrotrichia along the hind margin; anterior surface of hind femur with black macrotrichia on apical third or more of its length (
<figureCitation id="D29C48A5961E45695805F91BFD1DF94D" box="[581,660,1728,1754]" captionStart="Figs 47–52" captionStartId="14.[166,205,1411,1433]" captionTargetBox="[198,1192,174,1383]" captionTargetId="figure-160@14.[198,1192,174,1383]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figs 47–52. Epistrophe cryptica female:47 — habitus, dorsal view; 48 — apex of the hind femur, lateral view (arrow shows black macrotrichia); 49 — hind tibia, lateral view; 50 — head, lateral view; 51 — head, anterolateral view; 52 — head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6455546" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6455546/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="251">fig. 48</figureCitation>
). From 
<taxonomicName id="8DA72FA3961E456958B5F91AFC3BF94D" baseAuthorityName="Zetterstedt" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[757,946,1728,1754]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Epistrophe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanostoma">
<emphasis id="78D38832961E456958B5F91AFC3BF94D" box="[757,946,1728,1754]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="251">E. melanostoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it can be separated by: frons entirely black (
